[ti:Drizzle on the District Line]
[ar:Suno]
[al:Suno Review Album One]
[00:00.21]Half-price coffee, paper cup tilt
[00:12.44]Sleepless eyes in a charity quilt
[00:15.12]She hums softly, hood up, head down
[00:17.65]Phone light flicker on a cracked screen crown
[00:20.76]Bus stop gospel in a plastic bag
[00:22.87]Letters from the council, corners sag
[00:25.84]Kid in her belly kicks to stay known
[00:28.17]Name in a notebook, circled in phone
[00:31.16]Rain on the window, London sighs
[00:33.76]Everyone drowning, staying dry
[00:36.46]We all carry something on this line
[00:39.12]You hold your hurt, I’ll hold mine
