[00:52.68]Old man counting coins by tens
[01:01.16]Mouth full of dates, decades, friends
[01:03.90]Says, “Lived here longer than these bricks stand”
[01:05.46]Still feels foreign on his own land
[01:08.78]Knife scar peeking from his left sleeve
[01:10.95]War he never chose, now he can’t sleep
[01:13.16]Sends half his pension overseas
[01:15.97]Sits by the door, waiting on peace
